go over here.

00:32:48.320 --> 00:32:49.880
Next question.

00:32:49.880 --> 00:32:49.980
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:32:49.980 --> 00:32:51.080
My name is Justin Davenport.

00:32:51.080 --> 00:32:53.350
I'm with Virginia Tech.

00:32:53.350 --> 00:32:57.410
What I'm curious of is on this
same enterprise topic, has

00:32:57.410 --> 00:33:01.520
there been any discussion about
integrating H.323 or SIP

00:33:01.520 --> 00:33:03.320
endpoints into Google+?

00:33:03.320 --> 00:33:05.180
And have you looked
at any teaching or

00:33:05.180 --> 00:33:07.645
education use cases?

00:33:07.645 --> 00:33:11.350
CHEE CHEW: Can I ask you, what
is it that you want out of

00:33:11.350 --> 00:33:13.510
both SIP and H.323?

00:33:13.510 --> 00:33:15.900
AUDIENCE: Well, we have lots
of faculty that are looking

00:33:15.900 --> 00:33:18.470
for more advanced teaching
methods.

00:33:18.470 --> 00:33:21.670
And they see the commercial
technology of Google+.

00:33:21.670 --> 00:33:25.570
And they expect something like
that in the classroom or

00:33:25.570 --> 00:33:31.250
delivered online, something
beyond just a TV and a H.323

00:33:31.250 --> 00:33:34.490
link between two classrooms.

00:33:34.490 --> 00:33:37.230
CHEE CHEW: So I'm still not
quite clear on what is it that

00:33:37.230 --> 00:33:41.220
you want specifically from
the 323 and also SIP?

00:33:41.220 --> 00:33:41.820
AUDIENCE: I'm sorry.

00:33:41.820 --> 00:33:42.910
It's two separate issues.

00:33:42.910 --> 00:33:45.750
I guess the first question
is let's say if we had 20

00:33:45.750 --> 00:33:50.190
students sitting at home, a
faculty in their office, do

00:33:50.190 --> 00:33:53.740
you see a use case for that
for Google+ in the future?

00:33:53.740 --> 00:33:56.370
CHEE CHEW: This is actually a
very common thing that we will

00:33:56.370 --> 00:33:58.500
do, where someone will ask
for a specific piece of

00:33:58.500 --> 00:34:00.890
functionality, like, I
want SIP integration.

00:34:00.890 --> 00:34:04.320
And what we really want to do
is we want to dig in a layer

00:34:04.320 --> 00:34:07.660
deeper and say, hey, what is
the scenario that you want?

00:34:07.660 --> 00:34:11.670
And what I hear from you is,
we want to have the ability

00:34:11.670 --> 00:34:16.860
for teachers to have a
conversation, a class lecture,

00:34:16.860 --> 00:34:20.199
and for people at home, students
to not necessarily

00:34:20.199 --> 00:34:23.130
join in the Hangout, but also to
be able to consume it in a

00:34:23.130 --> 00:34:26.230
really cheap, easy, quick way.

00:34:26.230 --> 00:34:28.725
And we definitely want to
solve that scenario.

00:34:31.929 --> 00:34:34.080
Hangouts on Air is sort
of one format of that.

00:34:34.080 --> 00:34:36.330
Although currently, Hangouts
on Air require you to

00:34:36.330 --> 00:34:39.550
broadcast to the entire world.

00:34:39.550 --> 00:34:42.380
But the notion of wanting to
filter that down to a circle

00:34:42.380 --> 00:34:45.550
and broadcast that to a subset
is definitely something that

00:34:45.550 --> 00:34:46.790
we've heard the request for.

00:34:46.790 --> 00:34:49.270
And we definitely recognize
there is a need there.

00:34:49.270 --> 00:34:52.230
NIKHYL SINGHAL: So in my
opinion, I think there's

00:34:52.230 --> 00:34:54.800
certain use cases for Hangouts,
where Hangouts is

00:34:54.800 --> 00:34:56.380
always just a better answer.

00:34:56.380 --> 00:34:58.900
I think office hours are
somewhat broken today.

00:34:58.900 --> 00:35:00.720
And what I mean by that is
when I was in college--

00:35:00.720 --> 00:35:02.580
I know it was a while ago
but-- usually what would

00:35:02.580 --> 00:35:04.470
happen is a professor would
sit in their room or the

00:35:04.470 --> 00:35:06.530
teaching assistant,
and they'd wait.

00:35:06.530 --> 00:35:08.420
And then you would essentially
have a student walk in.

00:35:08.420 --> 00:35:11.560
And the student would walk in
maybe 20 minutes in, and they

00:35:11.560 --> 00:35:13.720
would ask a question about
problem set number two.

00:35:13.720 --> 00:35:17.030
He'd answer the question, and
then the student would leave.

00:35:17.030 --> 00:35:19.123
Another guy would come in and
ask the same question, and

00:35:19.123 --> 00:35:20.590
they would repeat the
same question.

00:35:20.590 --> 00:35:22.500
And what would happen is then
there was a handful of people

00:35:22.500 --> 00:35:24.450
that actually had gone to office
hours, who seemed to

00:35:24.450 --> 00:35:26.920
have the insight, and the
people that didn't.

00:35:26.920 --> 00:35:31.250
So in my opinion, every office
hour in the world for every

00:35:31.250 --> 00:35:34.930
institution should be always
run with a Hangout in mind.

00:35:34.930 --> 00:35:36.790
Because then you
can broadcast.

00:35:36.790 --> 00:35:39.340
People can jump in, they can
actually ask the questions.

00:35:39.340 --> 00:35:41.840
You could record, you
can play it back.

00:35:41.840 --> 00:35:44.916
You can clip the section that is
actually interesting, share

00:35:44.916 --> 00:35:45.910
it to the world.

00:35:45.910 --> 00:35:47.440
This we are committed
to doing.

00:35:47.440 --> 00:35:50.300
The product today actually
does a fairly good job.

00:35:50.300 --> 00:35:52.180
We're starting to see
people come in.

00:35:52.180 --> 00:35:53.720
There has been some concerns
around privacy.

00:35:53.720 --> 00:35:56.220
We haven't heard the technical
concern that you mentioned.

00:35:56.220 --> 00:35:58.690
But I suspect there is probably
issues around

00:35:58.690 --> 00:35:58.760
[INAUDIBLE].

00:35:58.760 --> 00:36:01.100
CHEE CHEW: But the way that
we're doing this, you could

00:36:01.100 --> 00:36:05.080
connect to it via a Flash
Player, or a video tag, or

00:36:05.080 --> 00:36:06.670
something really simple
like that.

00:36:06.670 --> 00:36:08.110
NIKHYL SINGHAL: So it's an
area that we're really

00:36:08.110 --> 00:36:10.090
interested in investing in.

00:36:10.090 --> 00:36:11.770
Medicine and education
are two of the

00:36:11.770 --> 00:36:13.650
verticals that we're really--

00:36:13.650 --> 00:36:15.130
I would say-- hyper-investing
in.

00:36:15.130 --> 00:36:16.610
STEVE GROVE: There's just a lot
of efficiencies when you

00:36:16.610 --> 00:36:19.090
start taking a Hangout from just
being the 10 people there

00:36:19.090 --> 00:36:20.180
and then making it a
broadcast Hangout.

00:36:20.180 --> 00:36:20.645
NIKHYL SINGHAL: That's right.

00:36:20.645 --> 00:36:22.110
STEVE GROVE: Let's
go over here.

00:36:22.110 --> 00:36:22.440
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:36:22.440 --> 00:36:23.100
Mike Corbett.

00:36:23.100 --> 00:36:24.520
Android Headlines.

00:36:24.520 --> 00:36:28.170
I was wondering if it would be
possible in the future--

00:36:28.170 --> 00:36:29.640
and I know you can't
talk about some

00:36:29.640 --> 00:36:31.580
future things, but--

00:36:31.580 --> 00:36:36.020
if Hangouts on Air was planned
for mobile in the future.

00:36:36.020 --> 00:36:38.290
CHEE CHEW: You mean
plan to join?

00:36:38.290 --> 00:36:38.820
Broadcast?

00:36:38.820 --> 00:36:39.280
I guess both.

00:36:39.280 --> 00:36:40.870
STEVE GROVE: This is also the
number two question on the

00:36:40.870 --> 00:36:42.120
Moderator right now.

00:36:45.260 --> 00:36:46.620
NIKHYL SINGHAL: Maybe I'll
club them all together.

00:36:46.620 --> 00:36:52.000
I would say essentially
everything that we do on the

00:36:52.000 --> 00:36:55.510
desktop, the plan and the
intention, is for us to have

00:36:55.510 --> 00:36:57.390
them available on
all surfaces.

00:36:57.390 --> 00:37:01.390
So as far as I know, we don't
have a single feature that is

00:37:01.390 --> 00:37:02.530
desktop specific.

00:37:02.530 --> 00:37:05.620
It turns out from a sequencing
point of view, as you point

00:37:05.620 --> 00:37:09.010
out, both our platform for apps,
as well as our Hangout

00:37:09.010 --> 00:37:12.860
on Air product line and our
feature set are the two that

00:37:12.860 --> 00:37:15.100
we don't currently
have supported.

00:37:15.100 --> 00:37:17.740
I think we took a big step today
actually by launching

00:37:17.740 --> 00:37:20.770
our tablet support, which had
Hangouts fully integrated,

00:37:20.770 --> 00:37:23.900
which is one of the most
commonly asked questions, and

00:37:23.900 --> 00:37:25.580
the mobile phone support.

00:37:25.580 --> 00:37:28.410
And for those of you that
haven't done a video call on a

00:37:28.410 --> 00:37:32.690
tablet, it's very different
than you may think.

00:37:32.690 --> 00:37:35.240
Think about where you hold your
phone, where you hold

00:37:35.240 --> 00:37:36.580
your tablet, and where
you hold your

00:37:36.580 --> 00:37:38.570
desktop in your house.

00:37:38.570 --> 00:37:42.630
So when you hold a tablet, and
you have a video conversation,

00:37:42.630 --> 00:37:44.720
and it's with your friends and
family, particularly those

00:37:44.720 --> 00:37:47.320
that you don't see very often,
you hold it on the left, and

00:37:47.320 --> 00:37:48.530
you hold it on the right.

00:37:48.530 --> 00:37:50.990
It's almost like you're hugging
the person, and you're

00:37:50.990 --> 00:37:52.050
in this conversation.

00:37:52.050 --> 00:37:55.410
That degree of intimacy changes
the style of the

00:37:55.410 --> 00:37:57.380
conversation.

00:37:57.380 --> 00:38:00.100
So we're really excited about
the fact that we're pushing

00:38:00.100 --> 00:38:03.380
now on all of our different
surfaces.

00:38:03.380 --> 00:38:07.070
But it is a clear investment
that we will have those

00:38:07.070 --> 00:38:08.400
capabilities.

00:38:08.400 --> 00:38:09.966
But we don't have it in a
time frame that we can

00:38:09.966 --> 00:38:10.305
announce right now.

00:38:10.305 --> 00:38:12.370
CHEE CHEW: Anytime when you see
something that's not on

00:38:12.370 --> 00:38:16.300
one of those platforms, the
answer why it's not there is

00:38:16.300 --> 00:38:19.040
almost certainly either a
technical limitation, where we

00:38:19.040 --> 00:38:22.070
can't, but we want to, or our
engineers just aren't typing

00:38:22.070 --> 00:38:22.600
fast enough.

00:38:22.600 --> 00:38:24.830
And we need to get them
to type faster.

00:38:24.830 --> 00:38:25.240
NIKHYL SINGHAL: More coffee.

00:38:25.240 --> 00:38:26.530
CHEE CHEW: More coffee.

00:38:26.530 --> 00:38:28.630
STEVE GROVE: A lot of the
questions on the Moderator are

