I think it's embedded in your
question, which is can I take

00:39:04.590 --> 00:39:07.060
a Hangout and make it work
on a television.

00:39:07.060 --> 00:39:08.940
It's a very classic question.

00:39:08.940 --> 00:39:10.530
It's a great question.

00:39:10.530 --> 00:39:13.040
With iOS, we're able to
start seeing that.

00:39:13.040 --> 00:39:14.510
Clearly, we're committed
to doing that on the

00:39:14.510 --> 00:39:15.450
Googlestack as well.

00:39:15.450 --> 00:39:16.690
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:39:16.690 --> 00:39:18.070
STEVE GROVE: You can imagine
putting your television or

00:39:18.070 --> 00:39:20.900
your tablet at one of the dinner
chairs at dinnertime

00:39:20.900 --> 00:39:22.810
and actually enjoying a meal
with somebody who's

00:39:22.810 --> 00:39:23.790
actually not there.

00:39:23.790 --> 00:39:25.256
Let's go over here.

00:39:25.256 --> 00:39:25.702
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:39:25.702 --> 00:39:27.040
I just want to follow up on the

00:39:27.040 --> 00:39:30.120
enterprise question before.

00:39:30.120 --> 00:39:34.150
So in large corporations, you
often have this meetings where

00:39:34.150 --> 00:39:36.930
you're broadcasting
to everybody.

00:39:36.930 --> 00:39:40.730
And it's a really expensive way
to communicate to folks.

00:39:40.730 --> 00:39:43.940
Hangouts offer another
solution for us.

00:39:43.940 --> 00:39:47.630
And I'm just wondering is there
a way to have folks join

00:39:47.630 --> 00:39:50.600
a Hangout without having to
have the participation?

00:39:50.600 --> 00:39:53.780
So if you can imagine
40,000 people

00:39:53.780 --> 00:39:55.810
needing to join a Hangout.

00:39:55.810 --> 00:39:57.970
We don't really want to have
40,000 people join a Hangout

00:39:57.970 --> 00:39:59.780
per se, but we'd love to be
able to broadcast and

00:39:59.780 --> 00:40:03.700
communicate with
them that way.

00:40:03.700 --> 00:40:08.010
CHEE CHEW: So if I could reframe
your question, I think

00:40:08.010 --> 00:40:11.050
what you're asking for is if you
want people to be able to

00:40:11.050 --> 00:40:14.070
join, but not actually
participate, but consume it,

00:40:14.070 --> 00:40:15.950
you're actually asking for
Hangouts on Air, but

00:40:15.950 --> 00:40:17.680
restricted to your company.

00:40:17.680 --> 00:40:18.610
Is that fair?

00:40:18.610 --> 00:40:22.120
AUDIENCE: Or maybe in some
ways participate.

00:40:22.120 --> 00:40:25.390
Maybe voting or something
like that.

00:40:25.390 --> 00:40:29.390
Just some ideas to help
out the use cases.

00:40:29.390 --> 00:40:32.990
CHEE CHEW: So the notion
of these use cases,

00:40:32.990 --> 00:40:34.820
I think, are great.

00:40:34.820 --> 00:40:37.445
It is a very common thing
that we've had a

00:40:37.445 --> 00:40:39.260
lot of requests for.

00:40:39.260 --> 00:40:43.030
What Steve has up here
is an app that

00:40:43.030 --> 00:40:43.990
we're actually building.

00:40:43.990 --> 00:40:45.280
It is using the platform.

00:40:45.280 --> 00:40:48.030
And what this does
is it combines

00:40:48.030 --> 00:40:50.050
Hangouts with Moderator.

00:40:50.050 --> 00:40:53.120
So someone can view a Hangout.

00:40:53.120 --> 00:40:56.910
And then at same time, over
there on the left side, they

00:40:56.910 --> 00:40:58.180
can ask a question.

00:40:58.180 --> 00:41:00.490
And then other people can
vote on that question.

00:41:00.490 --> 00:41:02.180
Oh, yeah, I want to
ask that question.

00:41:02.180 --> 00:41:04.780
And then the people inside the
Hangout, whoever's presenting

00:41:04.780 --> 00:41:06.760
on it, will see those questions,
and they'll see

00:41:06.760 --> 00:41:07.510
them bubble up.

00:41:07.510 --> 00:41:09.590
And they can respond to it.

00:41:09.590 --> 00:41:14.720
And this is a platform aspect
that we want to bring forth to

00:41:14.720 --> 00:41:17.340
allow scenarios that we were
just talking about, as well as

00:41:17.340 --> 00:41:20.160
many others scenarios that the
media has been asking for.

00:41:20.160 --> 00:41:23.020
AUDIENCE: So at Google, you say,
