00:41:43.640 --> 00:41:44.930
attend that meeting
and watch it.

00:41:44.930 --> 00:41:47.200
Yeah, there's no question
that we have that.

00:41:47.200 --> 00:41:50.550
NIKHYL SINGHAL: The use cases
typically either it's just a

00:41:50.550 --> 00:41:53.910
pure streaming use case, which
is a handful of people want to

00:41:53.910 --> 00:41:56.010
be able to speak, and
they want to be able

00:41:56.010 --> 00:41:57.510
to reach the masses.

00:41:57.510 --> 00:41:59.410
We get a lot of questions
around record.

00:41:59.410 --> 00:42:01.720
So the ability to have a
conversation, and have it

00:42:01.720 --> 00:42:05.090
recorded, and then be able to
play it back for future use.

00:42:05.090 --> 00:42:08.320
And then the third is the key
point that Chee raised which

00:42:08.320 --> 00:42:11.840
was when the audience is able
to be in that view mode, how

00:42:11.840 --> 00:42:14.360
can you have that subtle
interaction?

